So the boat gets to Limassol, and while we\rquote re waiting to disembark, and people are waiting - you have to go on small boats, because the boat can\rquote t come into the quayside, it anchors half a mile out, so there\rquote s a queue, and it\rquote 
s hot, and people are jostling and things, suddenly a young policeman appears in front of me, and asks my name.  And at this point, I think, \'93This is it!  The Cypriots are going to take their revenge on me, as a sort of hybrid British renegade.  I
\rquote m going to be in some kind of trouble in this place before I\rquote ve even stepped off the boat!\'94  (LAUGHS)  But not at all!  He\rquote s come to find me because he\rquote s my first cousin, and my father\rquote s written, and they\rquote 
ve responded, and he\rquote s come to take me \endash  in a privileged way \endash  ashore.  So I jump the queue, and he takes me in, walk through Customs, they all say, \'93Hello\'94, and he says, \'93He\rquote s my cousin, and there\rquote 
s his passport\'94, an}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid13792356\charrsid14965953 d I\rquote m through, you know!  Wow!  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
