t speak any English and are being translated for by the one or two who can, and they are my cousins, and they\rquote ve come all this way, I mean, a three-hour drive, in the heat, to collect me off a boat!  Which for a man who\rquote 
d had no brothers and sisters, and hardly any - a small number of cousins \endash  three cousins by one aunt \endash  this was pretty amazing.  Emoti
onally overwhelming.  Remind ourselves, [I had] just lost my mother, whatever I felt about her, lost my marriage. Here I am being taken into something. My marriage isn\rquote t over yet, it\rquote s still on.  It\rquote s still on.  We\rquote 
re in the dog days of the marriage, it\rquote s in trouble, but we\rquote re still trying.  So I haven\rquote t lost the marriage \endash  that\rquote s an error.  And they take me off to the village and I have a marvellous time in various ways.  
