 about ethical problems of detachment and involvement, and William Foot-Whyte learns about illegal or immoral acts by some of his informants, so you\rquote re not sure whether this is on.  And the fact that Firth was shrewd enough to g
ive me that permission \'85 There can\rquote t have been many people who\rquote d, at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid13792356\charrsid14965953  that point, done this kind of \lquote roots\rquote 
, [but] I don\rquote t like \lquote roots\rquote  or \lquote heritage\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10034445\charrsid14965953 
