There is a theory about anthropology that becoming an anthropologist is becoming able to do a successful cultural performance, so you sort of imitate your informants until you can almost pass.  I have a colleague, a Portuguese \endash  he\rquote 
s no longer an anthropologist.  He trained as a psychiatrist, Jose Cutileiro, at Oxford, and then having qualified in psychiatry, decided to do a Ph.D. in anthropology, and studied a Portuguese village.  And to describe his own book, he says that he was 
